Viewing the testimonies with this framework, the jury had the epiphany we’d expected: the stories contextualized how a girl could be led to make up outlandish claims.

This was a story of two victims: a young girl living in chaos of fractured relationships, emotional violence, abuse, feuding, and mental illness, and an innocent man who escaped that environment only to have his life potentially destroyed for doing so.

We used these stories to build a framework by which the jury could view the testimony of the alleged victim. The framework allowed them to see how a young girl could be influenced to concoct a shocking accusation.
We told the story of the household of the alleged victim’s family, and the constant physical and emotional attacks occurring between them on an almost daily basis.

We told the story of the client’s relationship with the alleged victim’s grandmother, and how he left the household because he could not tolerate her emotional and physical abuse, which was witnessed by her granddaughter.

We told the stories of the alleged incidents. The client’s version is simple: they never happened. The alleged victim’s story was  inconsistent and surreal, referencing horror movies, porn websites, bizarre behavior by her mother, and her grandmother’s hatred towards the client.
We worked on the story of the client - from his past all the way to his post-arrest interrogation, with not one scintilla of evidence of the behavior of which he was accused.
The attorney asked me to work with him because, as we’d done before, he knew that telling a clear and objective story is the only way to effectively state his case.

The public defender must walk a line of challenging the alleged victim without seeming to attack. Too weak a challenge and client is convicted. Going too hard at the alleged victim alienates the jury, and client is convicted.
In such cases, storytelling initially works against the client: the story being told is so horrific, juries are prone to conviction to avoid risk of freeing who they first think of as a monster.

(7/8) But acting alone, local police and prosecutors can only do so much. Powerful executive action at the state level can right these wrongs.

(6/8) Some large cities in the county made significant improvements. By the end of 2019, police in two cities sharply reduced their requests for marijuana prosecutions, effectively eliminating the racial disparity.
(5/8) In fact, racial disparity in marijuana referrals was worse in 2019 than in 2018. https://t.co/Qeca1sw3S7

(4/8) But even though there were fewer marijuana referrals, fewer didn’t mean fairer. Black people were still overrepresented in the cases that police submitted for prosecution.

(3/8) In 2019, the Dallas County DA's office stopped prosecuting first time, low level marijuana possession offenses. That year, police sent the DA's office 31% fewer marijuana cases than in 2018. https://t.co/9MDqhmmRwC

Only respect people who deserve to be respected..
Beautiful things happen when you distance yourself from negativity
Stop wishing for it and start working for it ..
Fear kills more dreams than failure ever will

Be patient.

Stay positive. 

Don't overthink.

Trust the process. .
Two things define you: Your patience when you have nothing, and your attitude when you have everything ..
Action expresses priorities..
I don't chase after anyone, if you wanna walk out my life then I'll hold the f**king door open for you.

Just remember, eventually the waiting and hard work will pay off..
When everything seems to be going against you, remember that the airplane takes off against the wind, not with it.. -Henry Ford
Be honest with me, you never actually read the Terms of Service or Privacy Policy..!!

The 4 L’s of life:
1.  Learn
2.  Laugh
3.  Live 
4.  Love..
There comes a point in your life when you realize who really matters, who never did, and who always will..
Never take anything for granted. Live your life while you still can, make the most of every opportunity..
Never allow waiting to become a habit. Live your dreams and take risks. Life is happening now..
If it makes you happy, who the hell cares what anyone thinks. Be you, Do you..
Quit listening to other peoples opinions when it comes to you. It's not how everyone else views you, but it's how you view yourself..
WORK HARDER ??
When you talk, you are repeating what you already know. But if you listen, you may learn something new..
Sometimes knowing how far you have come, gives you the motivation you need to continue. Remember that the next time you feel like giving up
Be grateful for every day and never let the small stuff get you down..
Know the difference between a goal and a dream..
Promote what you love instead of bashing what you hate
Don't under estimate yourself. Keep doing your work, your time will come one day.
Talking to someone with an open mind is like seriously my favorite thing because there’s never an end to what you can talk about and learn..
Your struggle is part of your story..
Live a life you'll remember

1 million excuses
or
1 million dollars
Pick one, it’s you choice ..
Sometimes it takes sadness to know happiness, noise to appreciate silence and absence to value presence
Sometimes people with the worst pasts end up creating the best futures
Don't waste your time with negative people who always bring you down..
The reason why people give up so fast is because they tend to look at how far they still have to go, instead of how far they have gotten
No matter what knocks you down in life, get back up and keep going. Never give up. Great blessings are a result of great perseverance..
Success begins with dreams, that turn into desires, which become actions that don't stop until they bring results
Keep people in your life who truly love you, motivate you, and make you happy. If you know people who do none of these things, let them go..
Think positive and good things will happen..
You can do anything if you have enthusiasm. Enthusiasm is the yeast that makes your hopes rise to the stars.. -Henry Ford

The uninspired

The unexcited 

The ungrateful. .
